Currently, I am serve as an Associate Professor II at the Technological Institute of Aeronautics (ITA), Brazil. My teaching and research activities span across three distinct academic programs: the Bachelor’s degree in Aeronautical Civil Engineering, the Master’s and Doctoral program in Aeronautical Infrastructure Engineering, and the Professional Master’s in Aviation Safety and Continued Airworthiness.
My professional experience encompasses Civil Engineering and Computing, with a focus on Operations Research, Computational Simulation, Airport and Air Traffic Engineering, Geoprocessing, Statistics, Econometrics, and Data Science. I have developed several web systems in R and Python.
My key competencies include:

Econometric Analysis using R and Gretl; Advanced Programming in R, specializing in data analysis algorithms and geoprocessing;
Development of interactive and dynamic web applications in R and Python;
Proficiency in C++ programming;
Data modeling through Machine Learning techniques.
